The article is a speech delivered by the Vice President of the United States, Kamala Harris, in San Antonio, Texas. She discusses the signing of the Bipartisan Safer Communities Act, which is considered the most significant gun safety law in 30 years. She emphasizes the importance of taking action to prevent gun violence and calls on Congress to ban assault weapons and high-capacity magazines. Harris also praises the organization Unidos and its leader, Raul Yzaguirre, for their dedication to bringing the Latino community together and fighting for civil liberties. She acknowledges the diverse backgrounds and aspirations of the Latino community and highlights their desire for good schools, jobs, safe neighborhoods, justice, and equality. Harris emphasizes the need for leaders to work with and listen to their communities. She praises President Joe Biden for appointing Latinos to high positions in his cabinet and working with Unidos to address issues such as vaccination, hunger, and small business support. However, she also acknowledges that more needs to be done, and urges people to vote and get involved in local governments to bring about the changes they want to see. Harris concludes by affirming her commitment to the fight for unity, equity, and love alongside the Latino community.